<article>
  <div class="row">
    <header class="span12">
      <h1>The Farmhouse Podcast</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="span6">
      <p>
        Friends and Family of The Farmhouse in Hollywood, California. Occasionally, we talk about things and now we're sharing those with other people.
      </p>
      <p><%= link_to "RSS Feed", podcast_feed_path %></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <h2 class="span12">Season 1</h2>

    <div class="span4">
      <%= image_tag "http://farmhouse.s3.amazonaws.com/podcast/images/the-farmhouse-podcast-cover.jpg", :alt => "The Farmhouse Podcast, Season 1 cover" %>
    </div>

    <div class="span8">
      <ol>
        <li>
          <h1>JSON vs HTML + Microformats</h1>

          <%= time_tag Time.parse("2012-10-08T21:13:-0700"), "October 08, 2012" %>

          <p>
            <a href="http://iamshane.com" title="The Internet Home Site of Shane Becker">Shane Becker</a> and <a href="http://SteveKlabnik.com" title="Steve Klabnik">Steve Klabnik</a> discuss using <a href="http://www.json.org" title="JSON">JSON</a> vs HTML + <a href="http://microformats.org" title="Microformats">Microformats</a> as API output.
          </p>

          <audio controls>
            <source src="http://farmhouse.s3.amazonaws.com/podcast/S01/01%20JSON%20vs%20HTML%20%2B%20Microformats.mp3" />
          </audio>

          <p>
            <a href="http://farmhouse.s3.amazonaws.com/podcast/S01/01%20JSON%20vs%20HTML%20%2B%20Microformats.mp3" title="Download Episode 1 MP3">Download MP3</a>
          </p>

          <p><b>Show Notes</b></p>

          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://twitter.com/veganstraightedge/status/255149033834823680">Shane's initial question tweet</a></li>
            <li><a href="http://Microformats.org" title="Microformats">Microformats.org</a></li>
            <li><a href="http://JSON.org" title="JSON">JSON.org</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/HTML_in_XMLHttpRequest"><i>HTML in XMLHttpRequest</i> on the Mozilla Developer Network</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div> <!-- .row -->
</article>
